Wash and dry all produce. Adjust racks to upper and lower positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{}. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced, separating greens and whites). Peel @carrots{3}, then cut diagonally into ½-inch-thick slices. Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes.

Toss potatoes and whole @thyme{¼%ounce} springs on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of oil. Season with @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} and plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven on upper rack until browned and crisp at edges, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, stir together ¼ cup @panko breadcrumbs{9.5%cup}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, and ¼ cup water. Allow panko to fully soak, then add @ground pork{10%ounce}, garlic, scallion whites, @meatloaf spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and @salt{}. Combine with your hands. Shape mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves and place on one side of oiled baking sheet.

Add carrots to other side of same baking sheet, toss with a large drizzle of oil, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place sheet on lower rack of oven and roast until carrots are tender and lightly browned and meatloaves are nearly cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @ketchup{2%tablespoons} and @hot honey{¾%ounce}. Set aside. Once carrots and meatloaves are done, remove from oven and sprinkle carrots with half the @brown sugar{1%tablespoon} (use the rest as you like). Toss on baking sheet using #tongs{} or a #spatula{}. Return to oven and continue roasting until sugar melts and coats carrots in a glaze, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once potatoes are done, remove from oven and add @butter{1%tablespoon} to sheet. Toss until potatoes are coated. Discard thyme sprigs, then divide potatoes, carrots, and meatloaves between plates. Drizzle ketchup mixture over meatloaf. Garnish everything with scallion greens.

> TIP: We used ½ tsp kosher salt for seasoning meatloaf.